cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST

The paper deals with PAC-Bayesian theory, which is a machine learning framework for analyzing generalization bounds. The paper introduces novel change of measure inequalities for two families of divergences, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents several PAC-Bayesian bounds for various classes of random variables, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
